@WebAPI_HostAddress = http://localhost:5284

### 1. CREATE PERSON
POST {{WebAPI_HostAddress}}/api/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jan",
  "lastName": "Testowy",
  "email": "jan.testowy@example.com",
  "phone": "+48 123 456 789",
  "gender": 0,
  "birthDate": "1990-01-01T00:00:00Z",
  "address": {
    "street": "Test Street 123",
    "city": "Warsaw",
    "postalCode": "00-001",
    "country": "Poland",
    "type": 0
  }
}

### 2. LOGIN - GET JWT TOKEN (Run this first to get token)
POST {{WebAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jan.kowalski@crm.pl",
  "password": "Manager@123!"
}

### 3. GET ALL PERSONS (Protected - use token from step 2)
GET {{WebAPI_HostAddress}}/api/contacts/persons?page=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..nSkQgQaad20SgsTSKorqUqt8F410YAfDhST-4BncgPc

### 4. GET CURRENT USER INFO (Protected)
GET {{WebAPI_HostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..nSkQgQaad20SgsTSKorqUqt8F410YAfDhST-4BncgPc